 and the blood from the press went out from the press as high as a horses bridle,
 one thousand,
 six hundred stadia.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I saw a great and wondrous sign in heaven:
 seven angels having the seven last plagues,
 for with these,
 the wrath of God is complete.
 And I saw something like a sea of glass mixed with fire,
 and those who overcame the creature,
 and his image,
 and the number of his name,
 standing upon the sea of glass,
 having stringed instruments of God.
 And they sang the song of Moses,
 the servant of God,
 and the song of the Lamb,
 saying:
 ‘Great and wonderful are your works,
 Lord God omnipotent,
 just and true are your ways,
 King of the nations.
 Lord,
 who is there who will not fear and glorify your name;
 for you alone are holy,
 for all nations shall come and worship before you and your judgments are know.’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And after this I looked,
 and the tent of testimony of the temple in heaven was opened.
 And seven angels,
 having seven plagues,
 went out from the temple,
 clothed in clean white linen,
 and girded around the chest with golden belts.
 And one of the four living creatures gave the seven angels seven bowls of gold,
 filled with the anger of God,
 who lives for ever and ever.
 And the temple was filled with the smoke of the glory of God and of his power,
 and no one could enter the temple,
 until the seven plagues of the seven angels were completed.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I heard a great voice from the temple,
 saying to the seven angles:
 ‘Go,
 and pour out the seven bowls of the wrath of God on the land.’ And the first one went and poured out his bowl on the land,
 and there appeared severe and grievous wounds on the men who had the mark of the creature,
 and those who worshipped his image.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the second one poured out his bowl on the sea,
 and it became like the blood of the dead,
 and every living creature,
 which was in the sea,
 died.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The third one poured out his bowl on the rivers and the sources of water,
 and they became blood.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I heard the angel of the waters saying:
 ‘You are righteous and holy,
 who is and who was,
 because you have judged these things;
 for they poured out the blood of the saints and the prophets,
 and you have given them blood to drink,
 which is what they deserve,’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I heard one saying form the altar:
 ‘Yes,
 lord God omnipotent,
 your judgments are true and righteous.’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the forth one poured out his bowl on the sun;
 and he was given the ability to afflict men with heat and fire.
 And men were scorched with great heat,
 and they cursed the name of God,
 who had the power over these plagues,
 but they did not repent,
 or give him the glory.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The fifth,
 poured out his bowl on the throne of the creature,
 and its kingdom became darkness;
 and they gnawed at their tongues out of anguish,
 and they blasphemed the God of heaven because of their pain and injuries,
 but they did no change their minds,
 and repent of their deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the sixth poured out his bowl upon that great river,
 Euphrates,
 and its water dried up,
 in order to prepare a way for the kings who were from the rising of the sun.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And as I looked,
 I saw coming out of the mouth of the dragon,
 and the mouth of the creature,
 and from the mouth of the false prophet,
 three unclean spirits,
 like frogs;
 for these were the spirits of daemons,
 performing signs,
 and they went out to the kings of the entire earth,
 to gather them for the battle of the great day of almighty God.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See,
 I come as a thief.
 Blessed is the one who is vigilant and preserves his attire,
 so that he will not walk naked,
 that his shame may be seen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he will gather them in a place,
 which is called in Hebrew,
 Armageddon.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the seventh poured out his bowl in the air,
 and a great voice was heard from the temple and from the throne,
 saying:
 ‘It is finished.’ And there was lightning,
 and rumblings and thunder,
 and a great earthquake,
 the magnitude of which had never been since man was upon the earth,
 so great was the earthquake.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the great city was divided into three parts,
 and the cities of the nations fell.
 And God remembered the great Babylon,
 in order to give it the cup of the wine of his indignation.
 And all islands fled and the mountains were found no more.
 And hail,
 as heavy as a talent,
 fell from the sky upon men,
 and they blasphemed the name of God because of the plague of hail,
 for it was exceedingly great.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And one of the seven angels,
 who had the seven bowls,
 came to me and said:
 ‘Come,
 and I will show you the damnation of the great prostitute,
 who sat upon many waters,
 with whom the kings of the earth engaged in whoredom,
 and those who lived in the land were intoxicated by the wine of her prostitution.
 And he took me in the spirit to a deserted place.
 And I saw a woman sitting upon a scarlet creature,
 full of blasphemous names,
 and having seven heads and ten horns.
 And placed around the woman was purple and scarlet,
 and she was decorated with precious stones and pearls,
 having a chalice of gold in her hand,
 full of the abominations and wantonness of her fornication;
 and on her forehead a mysterious name was written:
 ‘Babylon the great,
 mother of all the fornication and abominations of the land.’ And I saw the woman,
 drunk on the blood of the saints,
 and the blood of the martyrs of Jesus.
 And I was astonished,
 when I saw her,
 with great astonishment.
 And the angel said to me:
 ‘Why are you amazed?
 I will explain to you the mystery of the woman and the Creature which carries her,
 which has seven heads and ten horns:
 the Creature,
 which you saw,
 was and now is not,
 but is about to ascend from the abyss and will go to destruction.
 But the inhabitants of the earth,
 those whose names are not written in the book of life,
 form the foundation of the world,
 will be amazed when they see the Creature;
 which was,
 and now is not,
 but will come.
 And this is understanding for the one who has wisdom.
 The seven heads are seven mountains,
 upon which the woman sits,
 and they are seven kings;
 five have fallen,
 one is,
 and the other one has not yet come;
 and when he comes,
 he must only remain for a short time.
 And the Creature,
 which was and now is not,
 is the eighth;
 and he is one of the seven,
 but must go to an untimely death.
 And the ten horns,
 which you saw,
 are ten kings,
 who have not yet received their kingdoms,
 but they will receive the authority of kings with the Creature,
 for one hour.
 These will all have one purpose;
 and that is to hand over their power and authority to the Creature.
 They will fight with the Lamb,
 but the Lamb will overcome them,
 for he is the Lord of lords,
 and the King of kings.
 Those who are with him,
 are called and chosen and faithful.’ And he said to me:
 ‘The waters you saw,
 where the prostitute sits,
 are peoples and multitudes and nations and languages.
 And the ten horns which you saw,
 and the Creature;
 these shall hate the woman who fornicates and shall make her desolate and naked,
 and devour her flesh and shall consume her completely by fire.
 For God will place in their hearts,
 to do what is pleasing to him,
 and they shall act with one accord and give their kingdoms to the Creature,
 until the word of God is completed.
 And the woman,
 who you saw,
 is a great city,
 which has command over the kings of the earth.’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After this I saw the other angel descending from heaven,
 having great power;
 and the earth was lit up by his brightness.
 And he shouted with a loud voice:
 ‘ Fallen,
 fallen is great Babylon;
 it has become the habitation of daemons and the prison of all unclean spirits,
 and a confinement for all unclean and hateful creatures;
 for all nations have drunk the wine of the wrath of her fornication,
 and the kings of the earth have committed immoral acts with her,
 and the merchants of the land have become wealthy by the excellence of her delights.
 And I heard another voice from heaven saying:
 ‘Depart from her,
 my people,
 so that you do not become partakers of her sins,
 and do not receive any of her plagues;
 for her sins have reached all the way to heaven and God has remembered her iniquities.
 Give her back,
 just as she gave,
 and repay her double according to her deeds.
 In the cup which she mixed,
 mix for her the double.
 As much as she glorified herself in her pleasures and delights,
 give her an equal amount of torment and grief.
 For she said in her heart:
 ‘I am a queen and not a widow,
 I will not see sorrow.’ For this reason,
 her afflictions shall come upon her in a single day;
 death and mourning and famine;
 and she shall be utterly consumed by fire,
 for the Lord God is mighty,
 and he has judged her.’ 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the kings of the earth wept and beat their chests because of her,
 seeing the smoke of the flames;
 all those who had committed immoral acts with her and lived in luxury.
 They stood afar off,
 because of the fear of her torments,
 saying:
 ‘Woe,
 woe,
 that great city Babylon,
 that mighty city,
 for in a single hour your judgement has come.’ And the business men of the earth wept and mourned over her,
 for no one buys her goods any longer:
 goods of gold and silver and precious stones and pearls,
 fine linen and purple dyed clothes,
 silk an scarlet,
 wood from the citrus tree,
 and ivory vessels and vessels made from wood of great value,
 bronze and copper and marble,
 cinnamon and cinnamon bark and aromatic spices,
 ointments and incense,
 wine and oil,
 fine flour and wheat,
 cattle,
 sheep and horses,
 four wheeled coaches,
 slaves and the souls of men.
 For your fruit,
 the desires of the soul,
 has departed from you,
 and all the richness and splendour have departed from you,
 and they will not be found any longer.
 These merchants,
 who had been made rich by her,
 stood far from her because of the fear of her torments,
 and wept and lamented,
 saying:
 ‘Woe,
 woe,
 that great city,
 which was clothed in fine linen and purple and scarlet,
 decorated with gold and precious stones and pearls,
 for in one hour such riches have been made desolate.’ And all helmsmen and all who sail,
 and sailors,
 and as many as whose work involves the sea,
 stood far away and cried aloud,
 seeing the smoke of her conflagration,
 saying:
 ‘What else is like this great city?’ And they threw dust on their heads,
 and shouted and wailed and grieved,
 saying:
 ‘Woe,
 woe,
 to that great city,
 in which all who had ships in the sea were made wealthy from her opulence;
 for in one hour she is made desolate.
 Rejoice over her,
 heaven,
 and saints and apostles and prophets,
 for God has judged her with your judgment.’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And one mighty angel lifted up a stone,
 like a great millstone and threw it into the sea,
 saying:
 ‘With such force will that great city Babylon be cast down,
 and she will never be found again.
 And the sound of the stringed instruments and musicians and flutes and the sound of the trumpet will not be heard in you any longer,
 and all craftsmen and crafts will no longer be found in you and the sound of the millstone will not be heard in you any longer,
 and the light of lamps will no longer shine within you,
 and the voice of the groom and the bride will no longer be heard within you,
 for your merchants were the great men of the earth,
 for by your sorcery and potions all nations went astray,
 and in her was found the blood of the prophets and saints,
 and all those who were killed upon the earth.’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After this I heard something like the voices of a great multitude in heaven,
 saying:
 ‘Hallelujah!
 Salvation and glory and power to our God,
 for his judgements are true and just,
 for he has judged concerning the great whore who corrupted the earth with her prostitution and avenged the blood of his servants at her hand.’ And again they said:
 ‘Hallelujah!
 and her smoke ascends for ever and ever!’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the twenty four elders fell,
 and the four living creatures,
 and they worshipped God sitting upon the throne,
 saying:
 ‘Amen.
 Hallelujah.’ And there was a voice from the throne,
 saying:
 ‘Give praise to our God all his servants and all those who fear him,
 small and great!’ 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I heard the sound of something like a great multitude,
 like the sound of gushing waters,
 like the sound of great thunders,
 saying:
 ‘Hallelujah,
 for the Lord God,
 almighty,
 reigns.
 Let us rejoice with great joy,
 and give him glory,
 for the marriage feast of the Lamb has come,
 and his bride has prepared herself.’ And it was granted to her that she might cover herself with the finest white linen,
 splendid and clean,
 for the fine linen is the righteousness of the saints.’ And he said to me,
 Write,
 blessed are those who are called to the wedding feast of the Lamb.’ And he said to me:
 ‘These words of God are true.’ And I fell before his feet to worship him.
 But he said to me:
 ‘See that you do not do that;
 for I am a fellow servant with you,
 and one of your brothers having the testimony of Jesus.
 Worship God.
 For the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy.’
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I looked,
 and I saw heaven open:
 and a white horse;
 and the one who sat upon it was called Faithful and True and he does battle and judges in righteousness.
 His eyes were like flames of fire,
 and on his head were many diadems,
 having a name inscribed which no one knows except he himself;
 and he was clothed in clothing sprinkled in blood,
 and his name was the Word of God.
 And the army,
 which was in heaven,
 followed him on white horses,
 clothed in fine linen,
 white and clean.
 And from his mouth proceeded a sharp sword and with it he strikes the nations,
 and he will rule them with a rod of iron;
 and he treads the winepress of the wine of the furore of God almighty.
 And he has on his clothing and upon his thigh the name written:
 King of Kings,
 Lord of lords.
 And I saw one of the angels standing in the sun,
 and he cried out with a loud voice,
 saying to all the birds,
 which were in the sky:
 ‘Come,
 gather yourselves for the great feast of God,
 so that you may eat the flesh of kings,
 and the flesh of military leaders,
 and the flesh of great men,
 and the flesh of horses,
 and those sitting upon them,
 and the flesh of all freedmen,
